&lt;p&gt;Are you a new qualified or experienced band 5 who would like to join the new Acute Medical ward at Barnet?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to reconfiguration, we are opening brand new ward to support the health services for the elderly that are emerging as we go forward with the dynamic plans for the future services in emergency and continuing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer our new recruits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We welcome Newly Qualified and Novice Nurses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supernumerary orientation programme that will be individualised to your professional needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capital Nurse approved Preceptorship for Newly qualified nurses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to a variety of fully accredited university programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal Transfer Scheme (after 9 months in the department)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Accommodation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruta Kaceniene (Ward Manager) internal extension: 64201 / ruta.kaceniene@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
